SIMPLE: forewit
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Forewit
<hw>Fore"wit`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
leader, or would-be leader, in matters of knowledge or taste.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Nor that the <qex>forewits</qex>, that would draw the rest unto
their liking, always like the best.</q> <rj><qau>B.
Jonson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Foresight; prudence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let this <qex>forewit</qex> guide thy thought.</q>
<rj><qau>Southwell.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forewite</ent>⟦br⟧
